Prague's MHD takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
Wednesday, October 1, 2008, is written in the history of the Prague Transport Company the date when the first passengers enter the metro, tram and bus with an electronic bonus in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can be purchased at the moment for almost one hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy the 30-day, 90-day bonus and the annual bonus (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and simultaneously load it on their chip card at the Info Centers and Transport Company posts at the Metro stations, Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
The bonds can be purchased from yesterday on the Internet on the pages of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
The service, until the evening, was used by more than four hundred people.
Those who start using the Internet as a form of commerce can definitely start to forget about ticket sales posts at the metro stations, where so far they had to regularly queue to get out a normal ticket.
The bonus is purchased on the internet, and the Opencard card recharges it to some of the thirteen branch offices of the Municipal Library.
"In these places there is available to passengers a window with staff prepared to help interested people with the purchase on the internet and also with the reloading of the voucher purchased on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Apart from the library, it will also be possible to reload the electronic bonus in the Opencard on the automatic vending machines that are located in some of the halls of the metro.
What are these vending machines like?
They are red, they remind us of a ticket picker machine and the travelers will probably have already set themselves in them at the stations of the Roztyly subway, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Now there are five in the city but at the end of the year there would have to be eighty," Opatrný said.
The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver
The use of the machine, which will start working tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter in it the Opencard chip card and the previously paid bonus will be charged only in it.
The electronic bonuses from tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
In other words, on the circular trains and bus lines from the numbers 300 to 499 that mainly use the inhabitants of the localities of central Bohemia.
"On the trains attached to the integrated transport of Prague there are reviewers equipped with a reading card that will help confirm the validity of the time and zone of the bonus," explained the control of the tickets, Filip Drápal of the Ropid organization setting the schedules of the collective transport of Prague.
The circular buses have their reading cards mounted on the driver's locker.
Upon entering it is necessary not only to show the card to the driver but also it is necessary to accompany it with the Opencard at the place intended for it on the side of the Box.
With this, the driver controls the validity of the bonus.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the bonds there is nothing easier than to ask the driver for this information," Drápal said.
Passengers who do not travel on the circulation buses and do not remember when the validity of the bonus is over can go to the vending machines where the cards are recharged.
Here, on the machine screen, you will be shown the information about the validity of your document.
