He may speak in a quiet tone of voice, loose words, a whisper or the opposite (screams, cries, long speeches...).
In cases where the demonstration is very intense it would be appropriate to observe the child and consult with a specialist, to check if there is any question that is generating a lot of anxiety and thus giving him a way out.
We have said that it is a benign disorder, therefore it has no treatment, unless it is associated with another alteration of the dream that can be treated (e.g. if it is associated with sleep apnea or a stress table).
What you can do is take into account a number of very simple preventive measures such as:
Try not to excite the child much before going to sleep.
Therefore, seek quiet games and avoid TV shows or TV series that are either scared or a little violent.
With very nervous children and who find it very difficult to relax, relaxation techniques can be used to help them gain some inner calm.
This will help the child to have a quieter dream.
Once the dreams appear, try to keep calm.
Remember that they are harmless to the child and that the next day you will remember nothing of what happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake him up.
It is useless, because he is not conscious, and you will break his sleep.
Even if he's talking, he's sleeping and so he's resting.
Remember that if you are very distressed during various episodes you should consult or find out what is causing so much anxiety in the child.
If you understand what he says (which is not the most common thing), do not fall into the temptation to interrogate him to dream of information.
You won't get anything, because when you're sleeping, you're not aware how to organize your thinking.
You will also hear what he says, but you do not know what he is dreaming of saying that, so be careful how you interpret the information and the conclusions you draw.
Never tell the child that you can interrogate him at night to know his secrets.
Not even joking.
That generates a lot of anxiety.
In short, don't worry, it's nothing bad, it's an episode that lasts only a few minutes.
