Today, the European Summit for Equal Opportunities has been launched in Paris, its host is France, which is also president of the European Union this year.
Lívia Járóka, a Member of the European People's Party for Fidesz, in his message addressed to the whole, as one of the main speakers of this professional meeting, called attention to segregation in education, because it is one of the most serious violations which plague Gypsy children and is also the greatest obstacle to the prevalence of their interests.
