"The vicious circle of poverty, segregation and unemployment must be broken, and Roma children must be given the possibility that democratic space will be guaranteed so that they can contribute to the future of Europe as citizens of full rights," Jaróka said.
The objective of the European Summit for Equal Opportunities organized annually since last year's Berlin meeting in the sign of the "European Year of Equal Opportunities" is to ensure a unique forum to promote the abolition of discrimination and equal opportunities at European and national level of Member States.
